		<body>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName> <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April 5607</date>.</p>
			<p>[Hebrew]</p>
			<p>My Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p>It is not long since&#44; several of my friends <del>have</del> urged me to come out<lb/> publicly&#44; in your periodical&#44; with my opinion about the [Hebrew] which<lb/> are yearly brought form the <placeName>West Indies</placeName> to this country.  <del>So</del> much <add>so I am</add> disinclined <del>am I</del> to give publicity to any thing of a <del>disputatious</del> <add>controversial</add><lb/> nature in matters of our religion that I should not even now trouble<lb/> you&#44; but that the time is approaching when our yearly communications<lb/> are made to the <del>W. I.</del> <add><placeName>West Indies</placeName> for the new supply of citizens</add> and I think it <add>therefore</add> my duty&#44; for the sake of our religion<lb/> to state that these [Hebrew] are [Hebrew] &amp; there cannot be found any word<lb/> against <del>it</del> <add>them</add> in [Hebrew].  All rumours that were set afloat<lb/> against the [Hebrew] of these are founded in error &amp; misinformation.<lb/>  Now&#44; my Dear Sir&#44; I do not intend to injure the feelings of any<lb/> of our learned men&#59; I wish only the unity of Israel in matters<lb/> of religious observances&#44; and that our <sic>brethern</sic> of Israel shall not<lb/> be <sic>wilfully</sic> deprived from [Hebrew] without just cause.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(8)">I remain&#44; very respectfully</p>
		  <p rend="indent(8)">Your obedient servant</p>
		  <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">A. Rice</persName></p>
			<p>To the <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
		</body>
	</text>
